  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fertilizer Innovation Alliance</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(Uganda):  .The Fertilizer Innovation Alliance program aims to improve farmers&apos; yields and income per unit area through better access to soil testing services and affordable blended fertilizer. The program works with Akorion, a youth-led Information and Communication Technology company and the Ugandan National Agrodealers Association (UNADA) to improve farmers&apos; access to affordable, customized site-specific fertilizers and soil-testing services that will improve adoption of fertilizers in Uganda and crop productivity. The alliance will build a modern fertilizer blending facility to market appropriately sized fertilizer packages to farmers; promote improved fertilized uptake through demonstration plots; build capacity of middle actors to commercialize blended fertilizers; and build a sustainable network of distributors...</narrative>
  </description>
